translate:
Throughout the morning, flying rain obscures the mountains; 
Strolling along the corridor with wide eaves and drains. 
I have stayed here for ten days as a leisurely soul; 
Tramping on the mossy spots, leaving my footprints everywhere.

Just a short distance from heaven's face, we temporarily part;
The connection of two platforms with laurels is truly rare.
Together, we watch the soaring peng's journey in the clouds;
Happily, the fish hide among the dense seaweed.
We write about the upcoming Zhongshan Pu in clear governance;
We climb the tower and recite Xie Hui's poetry.
The important crossroads are enough to elevate the noble;
Let not the six phoenixes regret their flight.

Officially idle, I have become a burden; 
Accustomed to laziness, my heart accumulates regrets. 
The ancient well no longer has waves, 
Cold ash cannot spark any flame. 
Humbly living, I feel ashamed; 
Competitive pursuits are also distasteful. 
In learning there is no new achievement; 
I feel that I lack good company. 
You, my dear, have an impeccable appearance; 
Your character is free from any flaws. 
Worthless things truly deserve to be ashamed; 
Gradually, you become warm and moist. 
In the past, your words were highly regarded; 
Our hometown holds you in high esteem. 
Your reputation is founded on your roots; 
Your literary achievements are etched in lead. 
Fifteen years have passed since then; 
It's time for you to shine in heaven. 
How can you comfort me in my poverty and sorrow? 
We meet at an ancient barrier. 
As an official, you hold a low position; 
You rest your hands, holding back your wings. 
Casually, you stand beside the national doctor; 
Your words are like a diagnosis. 
Encountering each other, the clouds fill the sky; 
Barely, you tend to your musical instruments. 
Brightly shining, the solitary orchid; 
Deep within the forest, it guards its beauty. 
Would rather be deceived by wild grass; 
Enduring for the false pretenses of the moss. 
Who will tread the path of fame? 
Allow yourself to rescue those in distress. 
Small weeds do not have far-reaching aspirations; 
Their scent truly embarrasses them. 
Shame upon the Easterner; 
Starving, they seek sustenance. 
Because of you, I am moved to travel; 
My thoughts turn to return home. 
On the Western Mountain lies a field of stone; 
Effortlessly, cultivate its harvest.

Incompetent in foresight, my official duties are meager;
Lacking talent, I float through life on shallow knowledge.
I serve as a gatekeeper, following the steward's command;
I borrow grain from the river god, seeking his assistance.
Stopping the purchase of food to cross the border;
Facing the wind, I sail upstream, persevering.
Together for a hundred years, we are all travelers;
In harmony with the flow, we are but a floating boat.

In the willow market, I linger and love the outskirts;
Upon returning, my poetry and words are both clear.
In leisure, I gather and cultivate my entire being;
In old age, I see the world through my actions and storage.
Hating to let the chrysanthemums pass with the rain;
Drunkenly striking the tiles like thunder.
A thousand years of Zhang Han's elegant words;
But he didn't want fame in his lifetime.

Venerable night's stay at the shrine, an early appointment;
Town officials all go out to accompany the sacrificial rites.
Only where the sun's rays are buried in clouds,
Is when the mountains wear their hats atop their peaks.
Recent rains have been scarce, a good year is assured;
Please buy a thousand jugs of wine, from now on we'll find joy.
